metadata.name: Lianas #16
metadata.description:
This piece is inspired by op'art and physics simulation. A perfect structure is created at first and gets destructed by repulsing forces making the whole edifice deform itself.

Thechnically this work is a grid of nodes that repel each other. Each node on each row is connected to its neighboor with a digital spring maintaining the equilibrium.

A random number of repulsing nodes are placed randomely on each generation, making the lines move from their initial alignment.

Final image is generated in about 500 frames as nodes stop to move.

metadata.name: The Wintertime #105
metadata.description:
"The Wintertime" is a collection of generative art that captures the essence of the winter season in a glitchy and abstract way. The pieces in this collection are a visual representation of the harshness and beauty of winter, where the cold and barren landscapes are juxtaposed against the sparkling snow and ice. The glitches and digital distortions in the art add a sense of chaos and unpredictability, mirroring the unpredictable nature of winter weather. The collection celebrates the winter season in all its raw and untamed glory. Each piece is unique and evocative, inviting the viewer to get lost in the beauty of the wintertime.

The work was inspired by the drip painting technique of Jackson Pollock and the minimalistic elegance of Japanese prints. Combining these two distinct styles creates a visually striking and thought-provoking collection that pays homage to the masters while pushing the boundaries of contemporary art.

This collection is the continuation of GPTree: https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/17691

metadata.name: The Manuscript #54
metadata.description:
This unique collection of generative art that explores the mysteries of alien languages and ancient manuscripts. These works tell stories that we may or may not be able to understand fully, inviting the viewer to ponder the unknown and the possibility of other forms of communication and expression. The collection combines the ancient and the futuristic, using digital techniques to create abstract and surreal representations of these mysterious texts. The result is a captivating and thought-provoking collection that pushes the boundaries of contemporary art. Each piece is unique and evocative, inviting the viewer to get lost in the beauty of the unknown and to consider the possibilities of other worlds and other ways of communicating.

In this collection, the use of generative art techniques adds an element of randomness and unpredictability, mirroring the mysterious nature of the alien scripts and ancient manuscripts. The pieces are created through a combination of algorithms and human input, resulting in a dynamic interplay between the programmed and the organic. The viewer is invited to experience the art as an ever-evolving representation of the unknown. The glitches and digital distortions in the art add a sense of chaos and unpredictability, inviting the viewer to ponder the possibilities of other forms of communication and expression. The collection pushes the boundaries of contemporary art and invites the viewer to engage with the mystery of the unknown.

Press [S] to save a PNG image.

metadata.name: z-pattern : stacked noise #2
metadata.description:
This work is an exploration of pattern interferences that can happen in depth perception.

Each token is composed of 35 frames stacked in the z-axis. Each frame is a simple noise field with several detail levels displayed on transparent background.

The 3D stack is oriented at random for each token.

This work is interactive : you can press and drag your mouse around the canvas to explore different views and see several patterns.
